 The Nigerian Army Force (NAF) has directed the Accident Investigation Bureau, Nigeria (AIB -N) to commence investigation into the crash of the military aircraft that happened on Friday, May 21 at the Kaduna International Airport. Military plane crashes were previously investigated by a board within the Nigerian Airforce, without the intervention of the AIB, a body statutorily established to investigate air accidents and serious incidents in the aviation sector. In a statement released on Saturday, May 22 by the General Manager, Public Affairs of AIB, Tunji Oketunbi, the black box of the aircraft has been found and investigation into the incident has started. He said; “Investigators will download and analyse vital information contained in the recorders at the AIB-N’s world class Flight Safety Laboratory, in Abuja.”